<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honduras: Military Chopper Crashes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) -- A military helicopter carrying four
soldiers crashed into electrical lines Monday and plunged into a
hydroelectric dam, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Officials did not release the Honduran soldiers names, but said
U.S. and Honduran military crews were looking for the men.
</P>
<P>
   The soldiers were taking part in a U.S.-Honduras disaster relief
training at El Coyolar dam, and were returning to Tegucigalpa under
heavy rains when they lost contact with the control tower, said
Col. Daniel Lopez Carballo of the Honduran Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
   Tegucigalpa is about 120 kilometers north of the dam.
</P>
<P>
   About 430 U.S. and Honduran military officials are participating
in a series of water, land and air exercises, which started June 1
and ends Tuesday. The exercises are designed to train soldiers how
to respond to natural disasters and to combat drug smuggling.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
