<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 20; Nasdaq Falls 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 20
points in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a slim lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off seven points and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is up a fraction.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts expect Wall Street to bide its time while Fed policy
makers talk about interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Open Market Committee meets today and tomorrow in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Many analysts now believe the Fed will be content to leave
interest rates unchanged, given the slowing effects of six interest
rate hikes over the past year.
</P>
<P>
   Even so, market-watchers are looking for trading volume to be
rather light again today, as investors await the end of the Fed
meeting.
</P>
<P>
   There's one other item to watch for on the calendar today -- the
release of the Conference Board's Consumer Confidence report for
June, at 10 a.m. EDT.
</P>
