<HEADLINE> Dow Retreats in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were narrowly mixed in early trading
Tuesday as Wall Street awaited a decision from the Federal Reserve
on interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after the start of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 13.79 at 10,529.20.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 0.28 at 1,455.53, and the
Nasdaq composite index was down 8.04 at 3,904.08.
</P>
<P>
   The Fed, which has raised short-term rates six times in the past
year in a bid to cool off inflationary pressures in the economy,
was beginning a two-day meeting in Washington. A decision on
whether to increase rates a seventh time is expected Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Many economists expect the central bank to leave rates unchanged
because the economy has shown signs of slowing from its former
breakneck pace.
</P>
</TEXT>
