   Elsewhere in television ....
</P>
<P>
   INFAMOUS AND ILLICIT: For more than 16 years, Andrew Chambers
lied for a living, posing as a high-rolling drug dealer and
infiltrating some of the nation's largest drug trafficking
operations. But Chambers seems to have gotten carried away. His
recent admission to lying under oath about his criminal record has
not only destroyed his career, but may put scores of felony drug
convictions in jeopardy. Now, serious allegations of a Drug
Enforcement Administration cover-up have surfaced, with charges
that the government knew of Chambers' record and continued to use
him as an informant. Chambers steps out of the shadows to discuss
his career with ABC News correspondent Connie Chung as ''20/20''
explores how far the DEA was willing to go in the war on drugs. The
report airs on ''20/20 Wednesday'' at 10 p.m. Eastern.
</P>
