<HEADLINE> Singer Vic Damone Hospitalized  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Singer Vic Damone, in the midst of a
national farewell tour, canceled appearances this week at an
Atlantic City casino after being hospitalized with flu-like
symptoms.
</P>
<P>
   Publicist Rob Wilcox said Damone, 72, felt ill Monday morning
and was admitted to a New Jersey hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Damone, who recorded such songs as ''You're Breaking My Heart''
and ''On the Street Where You Live,'' is in the middle of a tour
that is scheduled to run until mid-2001.
</P>
<P>
   Damone canceled appearances through Friday night at the Atlantic
City Hilton Casino Resort. Those appearances will be rescheduled in
the fall.
</P>
