<HEADLINE> BC-NY--Weather Summary, 1st Ld-Writethru,136  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Clearer skies with less humidity were expected
Wednesday in
eastern New York, according to the National Weather Service.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Highs Wednesday will be in the upper 70s. On Thursday, it will
be partly cloudy north of the Adirondacks and to the south it will
be mostly cloudy with a chance of showers. Similar conditions are
expected Friday and into the weekend, forecasters aid.
</P>
<P>
   In western New York, clouds will increase Wednesday later in the
day. Thursday will bring clouds and some sun with a chance of a
shower or thunderstorm. Friday will be mostly sunny with highs in
the mid 70s. Saturday will bring a mix of clouds and sunshine.
Sunday will be partly sunny with a chance of a shower or
thunderstorm and highs in the 80s.
</P>
