<HEADLINE> Prescription contraceptives now covered for county employees  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) - Birth control pills and other
prescription contraceptives will be covered under Westchester
County's medical plan beginning Saturday, County Executive Andrew
Spano said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Like many other employers, the county had excluded
contraceptives from the list of prescriptions covered by its health
plan. But Spano and the county Legislature agreed earlier this year
to budget funds for contraceptives in the county's self-funded
health plan.
</P>
<P>
   Spano said women in their childbearing years pay as much as 68
percent more in out-of-pocket health costs as men, much of it due
to reproductive care.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's become increasingly important that we recognize the
specific needs of our female workers,'' Spano said.
</P>
