<HEADLINE> UNLV Extends Robinson's Contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS (AP) -- UNLV football coach John Robinson has agreed to
a contract extension that will keep him at the school through the
2002 season.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson led the Rebels to a 3-8 record in his first season,
breaking the school's 26-game road losing streak and its 16-game
overall skid.
</P>
<P>
   UNLV, playing in the Mountain West Conference, won a league road
game for the first time since 1994.
</P>
<P>
   Attendance also increased.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think the extension shows how successful the relationship
between UNLV and John Robinson has been for both sides,'' athletic
director Charles Cavagnaro said Tuesday. ''He can coach at UNLV as
long as he wants to be here.''
</P>
<P>
   Under his new agreement, Robinson, 64, will receive a 3 percent
raise and earn $365,000 annually.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson was one year into a three-year agreement, which he
signed in December 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson won a national championship in 1978 at Southern
California. As an NFL coach, he led the Los Angeles Rams to two NFC
championship games.
</P>
