<HEADLINE> Mexicans Kill Innocent Man  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN CRISTOBAL DE LAS CASAS, Mexico (AP) -- Villagers in southern
Mexico mistook an 18-year-old man visiting his fiancee's parents
for a robber and beat him to death with clubs and stones, officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   Augustin Lopez Lopez on Monday was leaving the house in
Tzontehuiwts village, 12 miles northwest of San Cristobal de Las
Casas, when he was attacked by a mob that claimed he had robbed a
store selling subsidized food, the local attorney general's office
said.
</P>
<P>
   The townspeople grabbed Lopez, tied him to a pole holding up a
basketball hoop and beat him.
</P>
<P>
   The attorney general's office said Lopez was innocent of the
theft, and authorities were trying to track down the leader of the
mob.
</P>
