<HEADLINE> Clinton Declares Disaster Areas  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton on Tuesday declared major
disaster areas in parts of Minnesota and North Dakota struck by
severe storms and flooding the past two months.
</P>
<P>
   The announcement brings federal aid to supplement local recovery
efforts in a seven-county area of Minnesota that experienced heavy
storms and flooding beginning on May 17 and 18 counties and Indian
reservations hit by flooding and ground saturation starting on June
12.
</P>
<P>
   The counties in Minnesota are Dodge, Faribault, Fillmore,
Freeborn, Houston, Mower and Winona.
</P>
<P>
   The North Dakota counties are Benson, Bottineau, Cass, Eddy,
Foster, Grand Forks, Griggs, Kidder, McHenry, McLean, Nelson,
Pierce, Ramsey, Ransom, Sheridan, Traill, Walsh, Wells as well as
the American Indian reservations of the Spirit (Devil's) Lake
Tribal Reservation and the Turtle Mountain Band of Chippewa.
</P>
</TEXT>
