<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-27 23:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polo Magazine May Ride Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Polo Magazine may yet ride again under its
old name.
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. 5th Circuit Court of Appeals tossed out a lower-court
ruling denying the magazine the right to use the name ''Polo.''
</P>
<P>
   The ruling orders the lower court to find a less drastic remedy
than forbidding the magazine all use of the Polo name.
</P>
<P>
   In August, a federal magistrate ruled the magazine, published by
Houston-based Westchester Media Co., caused consumer confusion with
New York fashion house Polo Ralph Lauren.
</P>
<P>
   But the 5th Circuit ruled there was no evidence of confusion,
and that the lower court erred in not allowing the magazine to
include a disclaimer that it was unrelated to Polo Ralph Lauren.
</P>
<P>
   ''Westchester is happy that the court finally realizes that
Westchester has the right to publish a magazine called Polo,'' said
Tom Godbold, the company's attorney. ''The bottom line is we feel
vindicated.''
</P>
<P>
   Attempts to reach Polo Ralph Lauren representatives by telephone
were unsuccessful Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Publication of the bi-monthly magazine has been on hold since
October because of the legal wrangling. Godbold said Westchester
intends to resume publication, but he was unsure when.
</P>
<P>
   Polo Ralph Lauren asked Westchester to drop the Polo name in
1998 when it changed from a small polo-oriented publication into a
slick, lifestyle-oriented magazine producing 1 million copies.
</P>
<P>
   Westchester sued the clothier to protect the name it copyrighted
in 1992 as the official publication of the U.S. Polo Association.
</P>
<P>
   The court also chided Polo Ralph Lauren.
</P>
<P>
   ''PRL products became famous by basking in the reflected glow of
an elegant sport. PRL now asserts that it, not the sport, is the
source of the glow,'' the court wrote. ''In a sense, PRL is biting
the hand that fed it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-27-00 2306 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
